      "patchset_number": 3,
      "line": 43,
      "message": "That was Toine's suggestion 😄 I'm not sure what to call it. To complicate things:\n1. XPath standard uses the term 'attribute'\n2. Yang uses the term 'leaf'\n3. we use xpath to query yang data, so should it be called 'attribute' or 'leaf'?\n4. we use both terms in our code base.\n\nWould it be better to call it attributeAxisLeafName, to be consistent with other 'LeafName' variables in this class?",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 6742,
        "name": "Daniel Hanrahan",
